.TH BWMENU 1 "2026-01-20" "1.0" "wofi-bitwarden-menu manual"
.SH NAME
bwmenu \- Wofi menu for Bitwarden
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bwmenu
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bwmenu
is a Python script that uses
.B wofi
to provide a graphical interface for accessing Bitwarden vault data. It requires a Bitwarden CLI server running (via `bw serve`).
.SH CONFIGURATION
The application reads its configuration from
.I ~/.config/bwmenu.conf
.PP
Example configuration:
.IP
HOST=localhost
.br
PORT=9090
.br
WOFI_CFG=~/.config/wofi/style.css
.br
LOCK_TIMEOUT=10
.PP
.TP
.B HOST
Address of the server where `bw serve` is running.
.TP
.B PORT
Port of the server.
.TP
.B WOFI_CFG
Path to the wofi CSS style file.
.TP
.B LOCK_TIMEOUT
Time in minutes for automatic vault locking.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.IP \(bu 2
wofi
.IP \(bu 2
wl-clipboard
.IP \(bu 2
libnotify-bin
.IP \(bu 2
bitwarden-cli (bw)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/bwmenu
The main executable script.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/wofi-bitwarden-bloquea
Script to handle automatic locking.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/wofi-bitwarden-mata
Script to reset the lock timer.
